{
  "texts": [
    "See Supplementary Table S3.",
    "FPR (False Positive Rate) and FNR (False Negative Rate) were calculated using FP (false positives), FN (false negatives), TP (true positives), and TN (true negatives), derived from the confusion matrix.",
    "FPR: FP/FP+TN.",
    "FNR: FN/TP+FN.",
    "95% confidence intervals for a population proportion were calculated using the following formula: CI=p±z*SE, where z= 1.96 for a 95% confidence level."
  ]
}